label.value: Fluorouracil/Interferon Beta
NPI - Periods of Feeling Shaky, Unable to Relax, or Feeling Excessively Tense

value.value: Neuropsychiatric Inventory (NPI) Does the patient have periods of feeling shaky, unable to relax, or feeling excessively tense?

label.value: NPI - Periods of Shortness of Breath, Gasping, or Sighing for No Apparent Reason

value.value: Neuropsychiatric Inventory (NPI) Does the patient have periods of (or complain of) shortness of breath, gasping, or sighing for no apparent reason other than nervousness?

label.value: NPI - Complain of Butterflies, Racing or Pounding Heart

value.value: Neuropsychiatric Inventory (NPI) Does the patient complain of butterflies in his/her stomach, or of racing or pounding of the heart in association with nervousness? (Symptoms not explained by ill health).

label.value: NPI - Avoid Certain Places or Situations That Make Him/Her More Nervous

value.value: Neuropsychiatric Inventory (NPI) Does the patient avoid certain places or situations that make him/her more nervous such as riding in the car, meeting with friends, or being in crowds?

label.value: NPI - Become Nervous and Upset When Separated From You

value.value: Neuropsychiatric Inventory (NPI) Does the patient become nervous and upset when separated from you (or his/her caregiver)? (Does he/she cling to you to keep from being separated?).

label.value: NPI - Show Any Other Signs of Anxiety

value.value: Neuropsychiatric Inventory (NPI) Does the patient show any other signs of anxiety?

label.value: NPI - Seem Too Cheerful or Too Happy for No Reason

value.value: Neuropsychiatric Inventory (NPI) Does the patient seem too cheerful or too happy for no reason? I don't mean the normal happiness that comes from seeing friends, receiving presents, or spending time with family members. I am asking if the patient has a persistent and abnormally good mood or finds humor where others do not.

label.value: NPI - Appear to Feel Good or to Be Too Happy

value.value: Neuropsychiatric Inventory (NPI) Does the patient appear to feel good or to be too happy, different from his/her usual self?

label.value: NPI - Fine Humor and Laugh at Things That Others Do Not Find Funny

value.value: Neuropsychiatric Inventory (NPI) Does the patient find humor and laugh at things that others do not find funny?

label.value: NPI - Seem to Have a Childish Sense of Humor

value.value: Neuropsychiatric Inventory (NPI) Does the patient seem to have a childish sense of humor with a tendency to giggle or laugh inappropriately (such as when something unfortunate happens to others)?

label.value: Cyclophosphamide/Doxorubicin/Fluorouracil/Streptozocin
NPI - Tell Jokes or Make Remarks That are Not Funny to Others

value.value: Neuropsychiatric Inventory (NPI) Does the patient tell jokes or make remarks that are not funny to others but seem funny to him/her?

label.value: NPI - Play Childish Pranks

value.value: Neuropsychiatric Inventory (NPI) Does he/she play childish pranks such as pinching or playing "keep away" for the fun of it?

label.value: NPI - Talk Big or Claim to Have More Abilities or Wealth Than is True

value.value: Neuropsychiatric Inventory (NPI) Does the patient "talk big" or claim to have more abilities or wealth than is true?

label.value: NPI - Show Any Other Signs of Feeling Too Good or Being Too Happy

value.value: Neuropsychiatric Inventory (NPI) Does the patient show any other signs of feeling too good or being too happy?

label.value: NPI - Lost Interest in the World Around Him/Her

value.value: Neuropsychiatric Inventory (NPI) Has the patient lost interest in the world around him/her? Has he/she lost interest in doing things or does he/she lack motivation for starting new activities? Is he/she more difficult to engage in conversation or in doing chores? Is the patient apathetic or indifferent?

label.value: NPI - Seem Less Spontaneous and Less Active Than Usual

value.value: Neuropsychiatric Inventory (NPI) Does the patient seem less spontaneous and less active than usual?

label.value: NPI - Less Likely Initiate to Initiate a Conversation

value.value: Neuropsychiatric Inventory (NPI) Is the patient less likely to initiate a conversation?

label.value: NPI - Less Affectionate or Lacking in Emotions

value.value: Neuropsychiatric Inventory (NPI) Is the patient less affectionate or lacking in emotions when compared to his/her usual self?

label.value: NPI - Contribute Less to Household Chores

value.value: Neuropsychiatric Inventory (NPI) Does the patient contribute less to household chores?

label.value: NPI - Less Interested in the Activities and Plans of Others

value.value: Neuropsychiatric Inventory (NPI) Does the patient seem less interested in the activities and plans of others?

label.value: Octreotide/Tamoxifen
NPI - Lost Interest in Friends and Family Members

value.value: Neuropsychiatric Inventory (NPI) Has the patient lost interest in friends and family members?

label.value: NPI - Less Enthusiastic About His/Her Usual Interests

value.value: Neuropsychiatric Inventory (NPI) Is the patient less enthusiastic about his/her usual interests?

label.value: NPI - Show Any Other Signs That He/She Doesn't Care About Doing New Things

value.value: Neuropsychiatric Inventory (NPI) Does the patient show any other signs that he/she doesn't care about doing new things?

label.value: NPI - Seem to Act Impulsively Without Thinking

value.value: Neuropsychiatric Inventory (NPI) Does the patient seem to act impulsively without thinking? Does he/she do or say things that are not usually done or said in public? Does he/she do things that are embarrassing to you or others?

label.value: NPI - Act Impulsively without Appearing to Consider the Consequences

value.value: Neuropsychiatric Inventory (NPI) Does the patient act impulsively without appearing to consider the consequences?

label.value: NPI - Talk to Total Strangers as if He/She Knew Them

value.value: Neuropsychiatric Inventory (NPI) Does the patient talk to total strangers as if he/she knew them?

label.value: NPI - Say Things to People that are Insensitive

value.value: Neuropsychiatric Inventory (NPI) Does the patient say things to people that are insensitive or hurt their feelings?

label.value: NPI - Say Crude Things or Make Sexual Remarks

value.value: Neuropsychiatric Inventory (NPI) Does the patient say crude things or make sexual remarks that he/she would not usually have said?

label.value: NPI - Talk Openly About Very Personal or Private Matters

value.value: Neuropsychiatric Inventory (NPI) Does the patient talk openly about very personal or private matters not usually discussed in public?

label.value: NPI - Take Liberties or Touch or Hug Others

value.value: Neuropsychiatric Inventory (NPI) Does the patient take liberties or touch or hug others in a way that is out of character for him/her?

label.value: Melphalan/Methylprednisolone/Vincristine
NPI - Show Any Other Signs of Loss of Control of His/Her Impulses

value.value: Neuropsychiatric Inventory (NPI) Does the patient show any other signs of loss of control of his/her impulses?

label.value: NPI - Get Irritated and Easily Disturbed

value.value: Neuropsychiatric Inventory (NPI) Does the patient get irritated and easily disturbed? Are his/her moods very changeable? Is he/she abnormally impatient? We do not mean frustration over memory loss or inability to perform usual tasks; we are interested to know if the patient has abnormal irritability, impatience, or rapid emotional changes different from his/her usual self.

label.value: NPI - Bad Temper, Flying 'Off the Handle' Easily Over Little Things

value.value: Neuropsychiatric Inventory (NPI) Does the patient have a bad temper, flying "off the handle" easily over little things?

label.value: NPI - Rapidly Change Moods From One to Another

value.value: Neuropsychiatric Inventory (NPI) Does the patient rapidly change moods from one to another, being fine one minute and angry the next?

label.value: NPI - Sudden Flares of Anger

value.value: Neuropsychiatric Inventory (NPI) Does the patient have sudden flashes of anger?

label.value: NPI - Impatient, Having Trouble Coping with Delays

value.value: Neuropsychiatric Inventory (NPI) Is the patient impatient, having trouble coping with delays or waiting for planned activities?

label.value: NPI - Cranky and Irritable

value.value: Neuropsychiatric Inventory (NPI) Is the patient cranky and irritable?

label.value: NPI - Argumentative and Difficult to Get Along With

value.value: Neuropsychiatric Inventory (NPI) Is the patient argumentative and difficult to get along with?

label.value: NPI - Show Any Other Signs of Irritability

value.value: Neuropsychiatric Inventory (NPI) Does the patient show any other signs of irritability?

label.value: NPI - Pace, Do Things Over and Over, Repeatedly Pick at Things

value.value: Neuropsychiatric Inventory (NPI) Does the patient pace, do things over and over such as opening closets or drawers, or repeatedly pick at things or wind string or threads?

label.value: Azapicyl

value.value: A hydrazine compound that has been investigated for antineoplastic activity. (NCI04)

label.value: FACVP Regimen

value.value: A regimen consisting of fluorouracil, doxorubicin, cyclophosphamide, vincristine, and prednisone that may be used in the treatment of breast cancer.

label.value: NPI - Pace Around the House Without Apparent Purpose

value.value: Neuropsychiatric Inventory (NPI) Does the patient pace around the house without apparent purpose?

label.value: NPI - Rummage Around Opening and Unpacking Drawers or Closets

value.value: Neuropsychiatric Inventory (NPI) Does the patient rummage around opening and unpacking drawers or closets?

label.value: NPI - Repeatedly Put On and Take Off Clothing

value.value: Neuropsychiatric Inventory (NPI) Does the patient repeatedly put on and take off clothing?

label.value: NPI - Repetitive Activities or 'Habits'

value.value: Neuropsychiatric Inventory (NPI) Does the patient have repetitive activities or "habits" that he/she performs over and over?
